quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  8,53,"That is because God is not one to change a favour He has favoured a people with, until they change what they have in themselves, and for that God both hears and knows"
  8,54,"As was the wont of Pharaoh's people and those before them! they said our signs were lies, and we destroyed them in their sins, and drowned Pharaoh's people; and all of them were evildoers"
  8,55,"Verily, the worst of beasts in God's eyes are those who misbelieve and will not believe"
  8,56,"with whom if thou dost make a league, they break their league each time, for they fear not God"
  8,57,"but shouldst thou ever catch them in war, then make those who come after them run by their example, haply they may remember then"
  8,58,"And shouldst thou ever fear from any people treachery, then throw it back to them in like manner; verily, God loves not the treacherous"
  8,59,"Deem not that those who misbelieve can win; verily, they cannot make (God) powerless"
  8,60,"Prepare ye against them what force and companies of horse ye can, to make the enemies of God, and your enemies, and others beside them, in dread thereof. Ye do not know them, but God knows them! and whatever ye expend in God's way He will repay you; and ye shall not be wronged"
  8,61,"But if they incline to peace, incline thou to it too, and rely upon God; verily, He both hears and knows"